-- Zambian President Sata Re-Assigns Ministers, Mail Reports
-- B y   M a t t h e w   H i l l
-- 2012-07-26T13:26:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/zambian-president-sata-re-assigns-ministers-mail-reports.html
Zambian President  Michael Sata 
appointed Transport, Works, Supply and Communication Minister
Yamfwa Mukanga to head the Mines, Energy and Water Development
Ministry, the Lusaka-based Zambia Daily Mail  said .  He replaces Christopher Yaluma, who takes over Mukanga’s
former ministry, the government-owned newspaper reported, citing
George Chellah, Sata’s spokesman. Minister of Local Government
and Housing Nkandu Luo becomes minister of chiefs and
traditional affairs, the Daily Mail said, without providing
reasons for the changes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Hill in Johannesburg at 
 mhill58@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
